#Prison Term (#1085): the enchanted creature can't attack; when a new creature enters
#under the opponent, may retarget the Term onto it. The bears (initially termed)
#attack and connect AFTER the Term moves to the freshly-cast giant - the bears being
#free is the retarget proof.
[INIT]
firstmain
[PLAYER1]
manapool:{1}{W}{W}
hand:prison term
[PLAYER2]
inplay:grizzly bears,gold myr,copper myr,iron myr
hand:hill giant
[DO]
prison term
grizzly bears
no
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto end
goto firstmain
gold myr
copper myr
iron myr
hill giant
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
choice 0
goto firstmain
goto firstmain
goto attackers
grizzly bears
next
goto end
[ASSERT]
ENDOFTURN
[PLAYER1]
life:18
inplay:prison term
[PLAYER2]
inplay:grizzly bears,gold myr,copper myr,iron myr,hill giant
[END]
#PARKED after 5 iterations: the cast + enchant work, P2's giant cast works, and the
#termed bears never connect (cantattack holding). The retarget-on-new-creature leg is
#UNVERIFIED: the may prompt's timing is buried under very slow phase advancement
#after the aura cast (each goto consumed ~10 ticks), so the scripted choice 0 never
#met the prompt. Re-probe with the phase-advance stall understood (possibly the
#@movedto may-trigger holding priority each tick).
